definition.value: Bleeding from the uterus that is abnormally frequent, last excessively long, is more than normal, or is irregular.
Bleeding in pregnancy that occurs before, during, or after childbirth. Bleeding before childbirth is that which occurs after 24 weeks of pregnancy.
Bleeding before 24 weeks of gestational age.

Decreased menstrual blood flow.
Extremely light menstrual blood flow.
A condition in which prolonged or excessive uterine bleeding occurs irregularly and more frequently than normal.
Prolonged/excessive menses and bleeding at irregular intervals.

Abnormal uterine bleeding that is not related to menstruation, usually in persons without regular menstrual cycle. The irregular and unpredictable bleeding usually comes from a dysfunctional endometrium.
Uterine bleeding that occurs during a time not associated with the normal menstrual period.
Sexual behavior involving young adolescents or children in a sense that is nonnormative and typically criminal in the given society, such as child rape in the contemporary United States.
Pleasure derived from being physically or psychologically abused, whether inflicted by oneself or by others.
The enjoyment of receiving pain or humiliation.
Sexual pleasure derived from being physically or psychologically abused, whether inflicted by oneself or by others.

Sexual practices or activities involving bondage, discipline, sadism, masochism, or acts of domination and submission.

A set of behaviors, customs, and rituals involving the submission of one person to another in an erotic episode or lifestyle. It is a subset of BDSM.

Undertaking or practicing the submissive role in BDSM activities.

Traditionally, a sexual fixation on a nonliving object or nongenital body part. However, the term has been extended in common discourse to mean any sexual behavior pattern wherein an "abnormal" degree of gratification is linked to a particular object, activity, quality, etc.
The sexual attraction to specific parts of the body.
A sexual fetish that revolves around a fixation upon a particular article or type of clothing, a particular fashion or uniform, or a person dressed in such a style.
A sexual fetish focused on boots.

A fetishistic attraction to people wearing prescription glasses, or a partner wearing prescription glasses, sunglasses, or cosmetic contact lenses, or the fetishists themselves wearing any of these glasses.

The fetishistic attraction to people wearing shiny clothes made of the synthetic plastic polyvinyl chloride (PVC) or, in certain cases, to the garments themselves.

A fetishistic attraction to people wearing form fitting stretch fabrics or to the wearing of items of clothing made of such material. Spandex garments are often worn by swimmers, ballet dancers, wrestlers, rowers, cyclists, contortionists and circus performers, and spandex fetishists may incorporate fantasies about these activities into their particular fetish.
A sexual fetishism relating to undergarments, and refers to preoccupation with the sexual excitement of certain types of underwear, including panties, stockings, pantyhose, bras, or other items.
A particular type of clothing fetishism in which an individual is sexually aroused by uniforms.

A pronounced sexual interest in feet.
A pronounced sexual interest in eyes, the eyeballs, or activities involving them.

The sexual fetish for hands. This may include the sexual attraction to a specific area such as the fingers, palm or nails, or the attraction to a specific action performed by the hands.

Alvinolagnia or belly fetish or stomach fetish is a partialism in which an individual is sexually attracted to the stomach or belly.
